div.p:
There be many things may moue vs to Mercifulnesse: first, because in shewing mercy, we imitate God: Bee mercifull (saith Christ) as your Father in heauen is mercifull. Luk. 6. 36. And so shall you be the childred of your Father that is in heauen. Math. 5. 45. If we call God our Father, and professe our selues to be his children, then let vs be mercifull as hee is;

 wee can no way so neerely represent God, as in being mercifull: a mercifull man is the best image of God, and a child of God in deed. Wee say, that Child is most like his Father, which doth neerest represent him in Face and countenance: Now, mercy in the Scriptures, is called the Face or Countenance of God: God be mercifull vnto vs, and blesse vs, and shew vs the light of his Countenance, and be Mercifull vnto vs. Psal. 67. 1. So they that are most inclined to Mercy, are most like to God, and no doubt, but they are Gods children. Such a mercifull man, such a child of God was Tobias, who sent out his sonne to fetch in the poore, which remembred God, to eate with him, and tarried for their comming. Tobi. 2. 2. Such a mercifull man was Iob, Hee deliuered the poore that cried, and the fatherlesse, and him that had none to helpe him, Iob. 29. 12. 13. 15. The blessing of him that was ready to perish came vpon him, and he caused the Widdowes heart to reioyce. Verse 13. Hee was the eyes to the blind, and feet to the lame, Verse, 15. He was a father to the poore, Vers. 16. He restrained not the poore of their desire, neither caused hee the eyes of the Widdow to


               faile. Iob. 31. 16. 18, 19. 20 32 He did not eate his morsels alone, but the fatherlesse also did eate thereof; he would not see any perish for want of cloathing, or any poore without couering, the loynes of the naked blessed him, because hee was couered with the fleece of his sheepe. Hee suffered not the stranger to lodge in the street, but opened his doores to him that went by the way. Verse 32. But now pittifull Iob, and mercifull Tobias are dead and gone, who imitated God, and bare the Image of God, in beeing mercifull, and no doubt were Gods Children, and many an vnmercifull Nabal is start vp in their steed, who thinke all too little to themselues, and euery little too much for the poore.
